						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the platform of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1[56]5, Prathiva (Prabhava), Māgha, śu. 5.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record a benefaction made by some Reḍḍi during the administration of Gaḍḍiyapūṇḍi Ayana to the god Chennarāya of Nallaballi.</p>						

						</summary>
